4  Covariance Data                                                4031 1451
==================                                                4031 1451
                                                                  4031 1451
   The covariance data was taken from the 92Zr evalaution in the  4031 1451
COMMARA-2.0 library [7].                                          4031 1451
  In thermal and resolved resonance region we made use of the     4031 1451
covariance formalism based on the kernel approximation along      4031 1451
with data in the Atlas of Neutron Resonances.                     4031 1451
  In fast neutron region up to 20 MeV covariance estimates were   4031 1451
calculated using the nuclear reaction code EMPIRE and the         4031 1451
Bayesian code KALMAN. The KALMAN code along with selected         4031 1451
experimental data was used to determine the correlation matrix    4031 1451
of the model parameters. Furthermore, additional parameters       4031 1451
scaling total and absorption cross sections were included to      4031 1451
prevent the unrealistic drop in the cross-section uncertainties   4031 1451
and, in some instance, to cover the spread of the experimental    4031 1451
data. The total cross-section uncertainties were computed as the  4031 1451
sum of elastic, inelastic, (n2n), and capture.                    4031 1451
